Dia. 03 Opponent's Vital Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The 1-2 vital point with White 1 is another powerful move, but not in this case.
\par
\par Black's connection at 2 is the \cf1\b vital point for living\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par It was the \cf1\b opponent's vital point\cf0\b0  as well.
\par Actually Black can also answer at A instead of 2.
\par }
